WEBVTT

00:15.849 --> 00:18.601
What do you say we roll out
of town, young David?

00:18.685 --> 00:20.061
Drive up to Joshua Tree,

00:20.145 --> 00:21.479
build a fire, camp out?

00:21.563 --> 00:23.231
It's like 90 degrees
in Joshua Tree.

00:23.314 --> 00:24.232
I'm not going there.

00:24.315 --> 00:24.983
So, what about Vegas?

00:25.066 --> 00:27.277
{\an3}Casinos are always
66 degrees.

00:29.362 --> 00:30.155
Hi.

00:30.238 --> 00:31.406
{\an4}DAVID:
We should go,
like, this weekend.

00:31.489 --> 00:32.615
Dance with me.

00:32.698 --> 00:33.825
(chuckles)

00:33.908 --> 00:35.618
I'm going to go dance.

00:41.124 --> 00:43.126
♪ ♪

00:49.090 --> 00:50.133
Hey.

00:50.216 --> 00:51.176
Sorry I'm late.

00:51.259 --> 00:54.137
{\an1}Those inseams really
Mm. you up, huh?

00:54.220 --> 00:56.389
{\an1}So, uh, how
is Wayne, anyway?

00:56.473 --> 00:59.184
Wayne? Oh, you know,
perfect fit model.

00:59.267 --> 01:01.603
{\an1}Mm-hmm. I shouldn't
be concerned by this, huh?

01:01.686 --> 01:03.813
That depends
on your inclination.

01:03.897 --> 01:04.813
What are you talking about?

01:04.897 --> 01:07.484
Wayne's gay, right?

01:07.567 --> 01:09.110
Okay, yeah, Wayne's gay.

01:11.404 --> 01:13.156
Hey, where's Matt?
Digging up dirt on my old man?

01:13.239 --> 01:15.492
Matt is trying
to do the right thing.

01:15.575 --> 01:16.659
Yeah, if the price is right.

01:16.743 --> 01:18.328
Come on.
This isn't Kelly's fault.

01:18.411 --> 01:19.871
No, it's okay.

01:19.954 --> 01:21.664
Do me a favor
and come by the house tomorrow.

01:21.748 --> 01:23.082
Keep the guy out of my face.

01:27.086 --> 01:29.172
Okay... A) Noah is going

01:29.255 --> 01:30.799
{\an1}through a really
rough time right now.

01:30.882 --> 01:32.342
And B) Wayne is so not gay.

01:32.425 --> 01:33.384
I know, I know.

01:33.468 --> 01:35.011
I was just buying you some time,

01:35.094 --> 01:37.013
so you can getOh.er your crush.

01:37.096 --> 01:39.015
Yeah. That could take a while.

01:39.098 --> 01:40.016
(chuckles)

01:40.099 --> 01:42.352
♪ Love coming down on me ♪

01:42.435 --> 01:43.353
♪ Love... ♪

01:43.436 --> 01:45.647
Gina, he's not
even watching.

01:45.730 --> 01:49.234
♪ It's rocking my world ♪

01:49.317 --> 01:51.694
♪ Whoa ♪

01:51.778 --> 01:53.863
Hey!

01:53.947 --> 01:55.031
{\an1}DONNA:
Gina, you okay?

01:55.114 --> 01:56.866
Hey, hey, listen.

01:56.950 --> 01:58.910
Can we talk for a minute?

02:01.454 --> 02:03.623
I'll take that as a no.

02:05.458 --> 02:07.460
(laughter and chatter)

02:18.346 --> 02:20.306
Hi.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.895
{\an3}Do you know that Dylan
fixed up this car for me?

02:25.979 --> 02:27.605
{\an3}(chuckles)

02:27.689 --> 02:30.191
Isn't that sweet?

02:30.275 --> 02:33.194
And the best part is...

02:33.278 --> 02:36.197
that it was gift to him...

02:36.281 --> 02:38.241
from guess who!

02:38.324 --> 02:39.242
(banging hood)

02:39.325 --> 02:40.743
Okay, okay.

02:40.827 --> 02:42.370
Okay, okay, okay.

02:42.453 --> 02:43.872
Come I hate him. car.

02:43.955 --> 02:45.081
No, you don't.
No, you don't.

02:45.164 --> 02:46.207
{\an1}Come on.

02:46.291 --> 02:47.709
Shh. You okay?

02:47.792 --> 02:49.961
Yeah?

02:50.044 --> 02:51.462
I think you might want

02:51.546 --> 02:53.548
{\an1}to find someone
to drive you home.

02:53.631 --> 02:54.924
Donna will drive me.

02:55.008 --> 02:56.384
Good.

02:56.467 --> 02:57.886
You're nice.

02:57.969 --> 03:00.388
(chuckling)

03:00.471 --> 03:03.224
How come girls never
go for the nice guys?

03:03.308 --> 03:05.310
{\an1}(sighs)

03:18.364 --> 03:20.199
I'm drunk.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.367
Yeah, you are.

03:23.077 --> 03:25.955
You feel sorry
for me, David?

03:26.039 --> 03:28.917
It's the only reason
why you came out here, isn't it?

03:37.508 --> 03:39.052
(sighs)

03:39.135 --> 03:41.471
♪ ♪

04:08.081 --> 04:10.750
♪ ♪

04:34.107 --> 04:35.108
♪ ♪

05:21.946 --> 05:24.407
Didn't Kelly tell
you I was coming?

05:24.490 --> 05:25.491
Yeah.

05:25.575 --> 05:27.702
{\an1}That's kind of why
I hung around.

05:27.785 --> 05:30.079
Um...

05:30.163 --> 05:31.706
{\an1}it's an environmental
impact report

05:31.789 --> 05:34.208
{\an1}from your father's company,
privately commissioned

05:34.292 --> 05:35.293
by Hunter Oil and Chemical.

05:35.376 --> 05:36.461
Talk to my lawyer.

05:36.544 --> 05:39.297
Look, Noah,
this isn't about you.

05:39.380 --> 05:40.548
It's about big corporations

05:40.631 --> 05:42.091
that poisoned people.

05:42.175 --> 05:43.551
Really? How much you making
on this, Matt?

05:43.634 --> 05:44.802
We prove fault with one company,

05:44.886 --> 05:45.762
the rest fall
30%, 40%? What?

05:45.845 --> 05:46.679
{\an1}Do you want to talk
about greed? Theirs kills.

05:46.763 --> 05:48.973
Why are you ruining
my father's name?!

05:49.974 --> 05:52.310
{\an3}Why?!

05:52.393 --> 05:53.978
Listen, he was a lousy father.

05:54.062 --> 05:57.440
The guy never knowingly hurt
anyone in his life,

05:57.523 --> 05:58.733
except himself.

05:58.816 --> 06:01.152
Well, you say he's a good guy.

06:01.235 --> 06:02.653
(tapping report)

06:02.737 --> 06:04.280
I say you should read this.

06:13.915 --> 06:16.501
{\an1}I've always used macaroni
in my art and...

06:16.584 --> 06:18.836
And I make fresh pasta.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.964
This matchmaking system
you developed...

06:22.048 --> 06:23.382
We call it
the Love Fisher.

06:23.466 --> 06:25.635
The best $49.95
I've ever spent.

06:25.718 --> 06:28.304
{\an3}Well, I guess that's it
for you two and personal ads.

06:28.387 --> 06:30.181
{\an3}I'm sorry to be losing
you as clients.

06:30.264 --> 06:31.349
We're not.

06:31.432 --> 06:32.683
Oh.

06:32.767 --> 06:35.311
Take care.
Good luck.

06:35.394 --> 06:37.188
JANET:
Bye.

06:37.271 --> 06:38.189
Another happy couple.

06:38.272 --> 06:39.649
Do you think a computer

06:39.732 --> 06:41.651
{\an3}can scramble strangers'
likes and dislikes

06:41.734 --> 06:43.319
and find a perfect match?

06:43.402 --> 06:45.321
They're not our only success.

06:45.404 --> 06:46.656
I feel responsible.

06:46.739 --> 06:47.740
{\an1}For what?

06:47.824 --> 06:51.661
{\an3}For capitalizing on the fact
that out there somewhere

06:51.744 --> 06:53.830
is someone who is
perfect for you.

06:53.913 --> 06:54.831
Well, what's wrong with that?

06:54.914 --> 06:55.832
It's romantic.

06:55.915 --> 06:56.833
Yeah, but what about

06:56.916 --> 06:58.334
the poor schmo you're with?

06:58.417 --> 06:59.502
The imperfect one?

06:59.585 --> 07:02.004
We're not telling people
who to be with.

07:02.088 --> 07:03.506
We're just expanding
their horizons.

07:03.589 --> 07:05.508
We're selling false hope.

07:05.591 --> 07:06.676
(sighs)

07:06.759 --> 07:07.677
The couple that was just here?

07:07.760 --> 07:10.680
She takes macaroni
and glues it to crepe paper.

07:10.763 --> 07:11.973
{\an3}He...

07:12.056 --> 07:14.851
thinks it's really beautiful,
and... and they love each other.

07:14.934 --> 07:16.519
Case in point.

07:16.602 --> 07:18.563
I'm going to go downstairs and
get a bagel. You want anything?

07:19.605 --> 07:20.815
No.

07:31.784 --> 07:32.702
(beeps)

07:32.785 --> 07:33.703
(typing)

07:33.786 --> 07:34.704
Age...

07:34.787 --> 07:36.497
sex...

07:36.581 --> 07:38.708
occupation.

07:38.791 --> 07:41.711
"After lovemaking,
do you prefer to talk

07:41.794 --> 07:43.796
or fall asleep?"

07:45.131 --> 07:47.592
Go right to sleep.

07:48.593 --> 07:49.927
(computer beeps)

07:52.805 --> 07:53.890
(laughter)

07:53.973 --> 07:54.891
Hey, Gina.

07:54.974 --> 07:56.058
Any messages?

07:56.142 --> 07:57.560
Uh, yeah, the, uh...

07:57.643 --> 08:00.062
{\an3}the Environmental
Protection Agency called,

08:00.146 --> 08:02.940
and they want you
to call them back and...

08:04.108 --> 08:05.526
Hi.

08:05.610 --> 08:07.862
They're going to fax over
the 1997 guidelines for you.

08:07.945 --> 08:09.739
I have a little toothache.

08:09.822 --> 08:11.115
Thanks for your concern.

08:11.199 --> 08:12.950
Well, since we're swamped here,

08:13.034 --> 08:14.368
Kelly's going to help us out.

08:14.452 --> 08:15.870
Yeah. I will...

08:15.953 --> 08:17.371
file, copy, answer the phone,

08:17.455 --> 08:18.706
whatever he tells me to do.

08:18.789 --> 08:20.249
And I happen to know
a good dentist

08:20.333 --> 08:21.334
who lives with my mother.

08:21.417 --> 08:22.585
{\an1}I don't have
any health insurance.

08:22.668 --> 08:24.629
Matt, you should just really...

08:24.712 --> 08:25.922
{\an3}(groans)

08:26.005 --> 08:29.300
You should call
the EPA-- it's...

08:29.383 --> 08:30.801
My filling came out.

08:32.303 --> 08:33.888
Mel has evening hours,

08:33.971 --> 08:36.765
and I'll tell him
that you're a friend.

08:36.849 --> 08:38.726
I didn't say we were.

08:38.808 --> 08:40.937
I just said
that's what I'll tell him.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.855
Thanks.

08:45.691 --> 08:47.443
(sighs)

08:47.526 --> 08:49.278
She's going to hate me forever.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.489
Well, she'll get past it.

08:51.572 --> 08:54.033
But she doesn't have to like it.

08:55.034 --> 08:56.410
(sighs)

09:01.749 --> 09:03.209
Hey.

09:03.292 --> 09:04.835
Wayne, hi.

09:04.919 --> 09:06.462
Haven't heard from you
for a few days.

09:06.545 --> 09:07.546
Yeah, I, uh...

09:07.630 --> 09:09.006
Well, are my,d of busy.

09:09.090 --> 09:11.133
uh, underwear ads
all over Times Square yet?

09:11.217 --> 09:12.802
(laughing)

09:12.885 --> 09:14.345
No, not quite.

09:14.428 --> 09:16.639
{\an3}I, uh, sent some
photos and sketches

09:16.722 --> 09:18.182
to a big manufacturer,
but I'm just waiting

09:18.266 --> 09:19.976
to see if they want
to bankroll me.

09:20.059 --> 09:21.018
So, we're done working together?

09:21.102 --> 09:22.353
Yeah, I think so.

09:23.396 --> 09:25.564
I think we have to be done
with everything.

09:27.775 --> 09:29.819
{\an1}You think?

09:31.904 --> 09:33.614
Uh...

09:34.907 --> 09:36.951
Noah asked me
to move in with him.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.495
And a couple of weeks ago,

09:39.578 --> 09:40.997
I would have done it,

09:41.080 --> 09:43.666
but now, because of you,
I'm not sure.

09:43.749 --> 09:45.626
Maybe that's why he asked.

09:45.710 --> 09:48.004
{\an1}Felt like you were
slipping away.

09:48.087 --> 09:52.174
He's going through a lot
of family stuff right now.

09:52.258 --> 09:55.094
He's... he's really alone, so...

09:56.554 --> 09:59.348
You know, I, uh, always wanted
to be an airplane pilot,

09:59.432 --> 10:02.810
a... fireman, a veterinarian.

10:04.103 --> 10:06.897
{\an1}But never... you know,
never a... a model.

10:08.774 --> 10:11.110
{\an3}Well, thanks for
making the stretch.

10:13.195 --> 10:15.072
{\an1}But I'm going
to miss this job.

10:22.955 --> 10:24.707
Don't move in with him.

10:24.790 --> 10:27.710
I hardly even know you,
but even I can tell that, uh...

10:27.793 --> 10:29.962
{\an1}you're not doing it
for the right reasons.

10:47.938 --> 10:50.775
{\an1}Noah, I'm glad you called.
Been a long time.

10:50.858 --> 10:52.568
{\an3}I don't think so,
and neither will you

10:52.651 --> 10:53.861
after you read this.

10:53.944 --> 10:55.863
Unless, of course,
you've already read it.

10:55.946 --> 10:57.365
{\an3}The part about toxins
seeping into the ground,

10:57.448 --> 10:58.449
{\an3}people actually
getting sick.

10:59.533 --> 11:01.452
{\an1}Yeah, I've read it--
recently.

11:01.535 --> 11:02.870
Recently?
It's two years old.

11:02.953 --> 11:04.372
You were my father's
right-hand man.

11:04.455 --> 11:06.791
The lawyers found it
in your father's personal safe.

11:06.874 --> 11:08.959
You're saying
he buried evidence?

11:11.545 --> 11:14.298
{\an1}The joint development
with Olson Oil

11:14.382 --> 11:16.550
{\an1}kept the company afloat
the last year.

11:16.634 --> 11:18.552
{\an3}Come on, he wouldn't
do this for cash.

11:18.636 --> 11:20.971
{\an1}He defined himself
by the company's success.

11:21.055 --> 11:22.890
When it finally went belly-up...

11:22.973 --> 11:24.225
He killed himself.

11:25.351 --> 11:28.729
{\an1}The report says that there was
just a chance of leakage.

11:28.813 --> 11:30.439
Or a chance
it would cause cancer.

11:30.523 --> 11:31.941
You're telling me
he took that chance?

11:32.024 --> 11:34.110
He wouldn't want you
to think of him that way.

11:34.193 --> 11:35.945
No, he'd rather die.

11:43.577 --> 11:44.745
(lively chatter)

11:44.829 --> 11:47.832
(blues rock playing)

11:53.587 --> 11:56.298
{\an1}Well, I'm up
a couple of hundred.

11:56.382 --> 11:57.800
And the rich get richer.

11:57.883 --> 11:59.343
{\an1}You just got to cut
your losses, bro,

11:59.427 --> 12:00.344
press your winning streak.

12:00.428 --> 12:01.637
Who're you calling?

12:01.721 --> 12:02.847
{\an3}I'm just checking
messages, man.

12:02.930 --> 12:04.181
The station's supposed
to be calling

12:04.265 --> 12:06.183
about some artist booking
or something.

12:06.267 --> 12:08.436
From the booth behind you.

12:15.526 --> 12:17.486
You get the one in the middle.

12:17.570 --> 12:18.654
Uh, no.

12:18.737 --> 12:19.655
Message from Steve--

12:19.738 --> 12:20.656
said it's not important.

12:20.739 --> 12:22.658
Something from Noah--

12:22.741 --> 12:24.660
I, I wasn't really
paying attention.

12:24.743 --> 12:25.995
{\an3}DAVID: See, there's, like,
five hang-ups on here.

12:26.078 --> 12:26.996
Man, it's got to be Gina.

12:27.079 --> 12:28.164
Hmm, what?

12:28.247 --> 12:29.957
Gina.

12:30.040 --> 12:31.834
No, David, I haven't.

12:31.917 --> 12:32.835
See, breakups are
kind of like a train wreck.

12:32.918 --> 12:34.962
You don't want to linger
too long at the scene.

12:35.045 --> 12:35.963
Yeah, whatever.

12:36.046 --> 12:37.047
Come on, we both know how long

12:37.131 --> 12:39.508
you hung out around Kelly
after you guys broke up.

12:39.592 --> 12:40.843
{\an1}Well, it was different,
you know.

12:40.926 --> 12:42.136
I've known her all my life.

12:42.219 --> 12:43.637
Gina and I--

12:43.721 --> 12:46.515
we've never been, uh...
platonic.

12:46.599 --> 12:48.517
If you don't
want to talk

12:48.601 --> 12:50.227
about Kelly, fine,
we won't talk about Kelly, okay?

12:50.311 --> 12:52.480
I thought we were talking
about Gina.

12:52.563 --> 12:53.397
We were talking about Gina

12:53.481 --> 12:54.356
and then we started talking
about Kelly

12:54.440 --> 12:55.441
and you got all, like,
you know, paranoid

12:55.524 --> 12:58.194
and the eyebrows were going
and it was ridiculous.

12:58.277 --> 13:01.697
{\an1}Great girls, both of them,
but both hands are played out.

13:01.780 --> 13:03.741
Besides, I think
it would be, uh...

13:04.950 --> 13:05.826
It'd be rude

13:05.910 --> 13:07.203
not to thank these ladies.

13:07.286 --> 13:08.412
I think you should
cut your losses.

13:08.496 --> 13:10.956
No, press my winnings.

13:12.791 --> 13:14.585
You know, from over there,

13:14.668 --> 13:16.420
this looks like
a much better place to be.

13:16.504 --> 13:17.796
Mind if I sit?

13:19.924 --> 13:21.383
MIKE:
Thanks for coming tonight.

13:21.467 --> 13:22.718
JANET:
No problem.

13:22.801 --> 13:24.720
{\an3}So I was just losing
the nerd mantle

13:24.803 --> 13:26.889
{\an3}when I won the
Math Maven Award.

13:26.972 --> 13:27.681
Science Genius, seventh grade.

13:27.765 --> 13:29.391
Presented
at the school assembly.

13:29.475 --> 13:30.643
Universal humiliation.

13:30.726 --> 13:32.728
You know, I ran

13:32.811 --> 13:34.230
into one of my teachers
while I was in Anchorage.

13:34.313 --> 13:35.523
AYeah.?

13:35.606 --> 13:37.608
I spent an entire summer
in Alaska.

13:37.691 --> 13:38.692
Okay, this is too weird.

13:38.776 --> 13:39.693
We went to the same college...

13:39.777 --> 13:41.904
Yeah, we love the same
off-the-market cereal.

13:41.987 --> 13:43.030
I've got to talk

13:43.113 --> 13:45.574
to someone about buying stock
in the Love Fisher.

13:45.658 --> 13:46.784
{\an3}Yeah, um...

13:46.867 --> 13:48.285
that would be Steve.

13:49.453 --> 13:51.747
My..Me, too.end.

13:51.830 --> 13:53.874
A... a girlfriend, I mean.

13:53.958 --> 13:55.084
Three years.

13:55.167 --> 13:58.712
Her name's... Janice.

13:58.796 --> 14:01.298
(groans)

14:01.382 --> 14:03.217
What are we doing here?

14:03.300 --> 14:04.885
Admitting
there might be such a thing

14:04.969 --> 14:06.720
as a perfect person.

14:06.804 --> 14:12.601
Yeah, and maybe
we're not going out with them.

14:19.191 --> 14:21.652
{\an5}MEL:
I'm sorry
I couldn't see you sooner.

14:21.735 --> 14:22.861
Oh, that's okay.

14:22.945 --> 14:25.739
{\an3}I was really grateful that you
had evening hours available.

14:25.823 --> 14:26.532
The filling is set.

14:26.615 --> 14:28.158
Just stick
to soft foods tonight.

14:28.242 --> 14:30.327
Okay, thank you so much.

14:30.411 --> 14:32.955
You know, there's
a process called bonding

14:33.038 --> 14:34.665
that'll restore
the enamel you've lost

14:34.748 --> 14:35.833
on the inside of your teeth.

14:35.916 --> 14:37.835
Okay, well,
I'll check into that.

14:37.918 --> 14:40.504
I just have to get
some insurance.

14:40.588 --> 14:42.715
You've waited
a long time already.

14:44.091 --> 14:46.802
How long have you been bulimic?

14:46.885 --> 14:48.470
What?

14:48.554 --> 14:50.806
You obviously have
an eating disorder.

14:50.889 --> 14:53.809
The stomach acid strips
the enamel.

14:53.892 --> 14:54.810
You've been making
yourself sick,

14:54.893 --> 14:56.729
and you've been doing it
for a very long time.

14:56.812 --> 14:58.314
Um, do you know what?
I have my checkbook here,

14:58.397 --> 15:00.149
so do you want me
to just pay you now?

15:00.232 --> 15:01.317
Or I can have...

15:01.400 --> 15:02.651
I'll give you the name
of an internist.

15:02.735 --> 15:04.153
{\an1}You could have
esophageal damage,

15:04.236 --> 15:05.988
severe vitamin loss.

15:06.071 --> 15:07.698
Look, I don't really know
what you're talking about.

15:07.781 --> 15:10.492
I'm fine.

15:10.576 --> 15:12.828
You look fine,

15:12.911 --> 15:15.122
but you could drop dead tomorrow
from heart failure.

15:18.250 --> 15:20.169
Well, with the week
that I've been having...

15:20.252 --> 15:21.712
(chuckles)

15:21.795 --> 15:22.838
...that would be a relief.

15:37.394 --> 15:38.479
Dylan, open up, man.

15:38.562 --> 15:39.688
I won, like, $80.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.565
I put $1.50
in the machine downstairs.

15:41.649 --> 15:42.900
It was crazy.

15:42.983 --> 15:44.485
Come on.

15:45.778 --> 15:46.695
Hi.

15:46.779 --> 15:48.238
Hi.

15:48.322 --> 15:49.907
Come on in.

16:03.170 --> 16:07.132
{\an3}Hey, um, you remember Mary
from last night, David?

16:07.216 --> 16:08.300
Oh, sure.

16:08.384 --> 16:09.426
So I'm gonna go talk

16:09.510 --> 16:10.594
to Mm-hmm....

16:10.678 --> 16:11.887
...see if I can
get Mm-hmm.k...

16:11.970 --> 16:12.888
{\an1}...and then
I'm gonna come back.

16:12.971 --> 16:14.264
How's an hour?

16:14.348 --> 16:16.100
That's, uh, that's great.

16:16.183 --> 16:17.768
Good.

16:17.851 --> 16:19.895
Oh, I hope
you guys brought sunscreen.

16:21.355 --> 16:22.731
{\an3}(chuckles)

16:22.815 --> 16:24.733
That's, that's Mary.

16:24.817 --> 16:27.903
She... she knows
a, uh, unmarked trail

16:27.986 --> 16:29.571
that, uh, leads all the way
to Hoover Dam.

16:29.655 --> 16:31.073
{\an1}I don't know
how you do it, man.

16:31.156 --> 16:33.409
They just, like, flock to you.

16:33.492 --> 16:34.410
Well, you know, David,

16:34.493 --> 16:36.704
it's, uh, it's a gift actually.

16:36.787 --> 16:38.414
It's kind of
a curse, too.

16:38.497 --> 16:40.416
Well, I sure wish
you'd pass the torch.

16:40.499 --> 16:42.292
I will at breakfast--
oh, which reminds me,

16:42.376 --> 16:44.420
{\an3}I told Mary that I might
be coming back to town

16:44.503 --> 16:47.256
{\an3}in a couple of weeks
on business, so, you know...

16:47.339 --> 16:48.257
Get out of here.

16:48.340 --> 16:49.299
You lied to her?

16:49.383 --> 16:50.300
{\an3}Oh, yeah.

16:50.384 --> 16:51.301
{\an3}Back me up on that,
will you?

16:51.385 --> 16:54.430
{\an3}Come on.

17:06.650 --> 17:07.776
It's a little crooked.

17:07.859 --> 17:11.613
Oh, look,
I found this in a drawer.

17:11.696 --> 17:12.614
I didn't even know

17:12.698 --> 17:14.282
I still had it.

17:14.366 --> 17:15.784
Toastie Bun Buns?

17:15.867 --> 17:17.453
I haven't seen those in...

17:17.536 --> 17:19.246
Seven years, yeah.

17:19.329 --> 17:21.457
{\an3}I ran into
a friend of mine,

17:21.540 --> 17:23.083
who got me in touch
with the distributor,

17:23.166 --> 17:24.710
and I bought a case.

17:25.877 --> 17:26.962
No.you want some?

17:27.045 --> 17:28.213
I'm a Pop Tart guy.

17:29.298 --> 17:31.300
{\an1}Look, I tried
to call you last night.

17:31.383 --> 17:32.760
Yeah, I was out late

17:32.843 --> 17:33.969
getting that framed.

17:34.052 --> 17:35.137
{\an1}Hmm.

17:35.220 --> 17:36.305
Maybe we can practice

17:36.388 --> 17:37.681
a little long division later,

17:37.765 --> 17:39.057
but in the meantime, you're late

17:39.141 --> 17:40.809
I was out with a guy named Mike.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.060
{\an3}Okay?

17:42.144 --> 17:43.479
He's a Science Genius

17:43.562 --> 17:44.772
and he likes Toastie Bun Buns.

17:44.855 --> 17:47.024
The Love Fisher--
you couldn't resist.

17:47.107 --> 17:48.484
It was strictly anthropological.

17:48.567 --> 17:49.943
I can't believe you did that.

17:50.027 --> 17:52.362
Believe me,
I'm, I'm sorry I did.

17:52.446 --> 17:53.864
Well, that hurts.

17:55.199 --> 17:56.450
You have fun?

17:56.533 --> 17:59.161
It was by the numbers perfect.

17:59.244 --> 18:01.455
Of course it was;
you're the Math Maven.

18:01.538 --> 18:03.457
And it was--

18:03.540 --> 18:06.376
{\an3}it was by the
numbers boring, too,

18:06.460 --> 18:09.630
because I don't want
to date another me.

18:09.713 --> 18:12.299
Steve, it was...

18:12.382 --> 18:13.175
an experiment,

18:13.258 --> 18:16.470
{\an1}and I learned
that I have already found

18:16.553 --> 18:19.389
my perfect mate-- you.

18:22.392 --> 18:24.311
You're late for
color spotting.

18:24.394 --> 18:26.271
{\an3}Your breath smells
like Toastie Bun Buns.

18:26.355 --> 18:27.564
Right.

18:27.648 --> 18:29.525
Sorry.

18:44.164 --> 18:46.083
DYLAN:
This is Dylan.

18:46.166 --> 18:47.084
Leav(beeps)sage.

18:47.167 --> 18:50.420
(clicks)

18:50.504 --> 18:51.839
(speed-dial tone)

18:51.922 --> 18:52.840
(line rings)

18:52.923 --> 18:53.841
This is Dylan.

18:53.924 --> 18:55.342
Leav(beeps)sage.

18:55.425 --> 18:56.426
(clicks)

18:57.636 --> 18:59.096
Hey.

18:59.179 --> 19:00.722
Where is Matt?

19:00.806 --> 19:02.349
{\an3}Oh, he is meeting
with, um,

19:02.432 --> 19:03.433
{\an3}doctors and medical
researchers.

19:03.517 --> 19:04.560
He'll be in in a while.

19:04.643 --> 19:06.311
I can't eat.

19:06.395 --> 19:07.396
A new filling, you know.

19:07.479 --> 19:09.523
Actually, that was for Matt.

19:09.606 --> 19:11.066
Oh.
(chuckles)

19:11.149 --> 19:15.070
Listen, Gina... I'm sorry.

19:15.153 --> 19:19.241
Oh, is this the little talk that
you've been wanting to have?

19:19.324 --> 19:21.910
{\an1}Kelly, you slept
with my boyfriend.

19:21.994 --> 19:23.412
{\an1}I think
that about covers it.

19:23.495 --> 19:25.247
If I could take it back,
I would.

19:25.330 --> 19:27.082
{\an1}Oh, so now you're
going to apologize?

19:27.165 --> 19:28.083
Wow, that's great.

19:28.166 --> 19:31.295
Now I really see
how truly wonderful you are.

19:31.378 --> 19:34.548
{\an3}If being around me
is making it harder on you,

19:34.631 --> 19:37.426
then maybe we should rethink
the roommate situation.

19:37.509 --> 19:38.468
{\an1}I'm having
enough trouble

19:38.552 --> 19:40.929
trying to get through the day
without screaming,

19:41.013 --> 19:41.972
so the last thing I need

19:42.055 --> 19:44.266
is to go out and look
for another place to live.

19:44.349 --> 19:45.601
I apologized

19:45.684 --> 19:46.602
and I meant it,

19:46.685 --> 19:47.728
and you can accept that

19:47.811 --> 19:49.062
or you can leave.

19:49.146 --> 19:51.148
It's up to you.

20:19.509 --> 20:23.305
{\an3}Why don't you and I go
take a look at the house,

20:23.388 --> 20:27.309
kind of size it up
from the outside?

20:27.392 --> 20:29.478
{\an1}(sighs)

20:29.561 --> 20:30.938
Moving in-- it's just,

20:31.021 --> 20:35.442
it's a big deal, you know?

20:35.525 --> 20:37.611
Don't be mad, okay, but I just--

20:37.694 --> 20:40.489
I feel like you're pushing this
for the wrong reasons.

20:40.572 --> 20:42.115
Look, I want to be with you.

20:42.199 --> 20:44.284
{\an3}If you don't feel the same
way, wh-why are we together?

20:44.368 --> 20:47.120
Does it have to be
all or nothing?

20:47.204 --> 20:49.289
I mean, at some point, yeah.

20:49.373 --> 20:52.459
{\an3}Look, the realtor said there's
other applications, okay?

20:52.542 --> 20:55.545
If we don't call him back
by 7:00, it's gone.

20:57.297 --> 20:58.799
Look, I know what I want here.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.010
You figure out what you want,

21:02.094 --> 21:04.554
you call the realtor, okay?

21:10.769 --> 21:14.022
(door opens, bell rings)

21:14.106 --> 21:16.191
(door closes)

21:20.112 --> 21:21.905
(door opens)

21:21.989 --> 21:24.700
Hey, are you ready to go?

21:24.783 --> 21:26.034
Yeah, I checked
us out already.

21:26.118 --> 21:27.035
Get out of here.

21:27.119 --> 21:28.286
Let me give you
some cash, man.

21:28.370 --> 21:29.871
No, no, man, it's on
me, it's all right.

21:29.955 --> 21:31.415
{\an1}Yeah.ure?

21:31.498 --> 21:32.874
{\an1}Hey, you know that hike
that we went on,

21:32.958 --> 21:33.959
that Mary told us about?

21:34.042 --> 21:36.086
{\an1}That was a lot of fun;
I wish she could have made it.

21:36.169 --> 21:38.255
{\an3}Well, to tell you the truth,
I kind of like the quiet.

21:38.338 --> 21:40.215
{\an1}What, did she talk
too much?

21:40.298 --> 21:41.842
{\an3}Oh, God, are you kidding
me? "Wh-Where are you from?

21:41.925 --> 21:44.052
{\an3}Do you have any
brothers or sisters?"

21:44.136 --> 21:46.930
{\an1}She probably just wanted
to know who she slept with.

21:47.014 --> 21:49.307
(knocking)

21:51.518 --> 21:53.729
Uh... hi.

21:53.812 --> 21:55.272
I got your message.

21:55.355 --> 21:56.732
I wanted to say good-bye.

21:56.815 --> 21:59.526
I didn't mean
to pull you away from work.

21:59.609 --> 22:01.069
I'm on my lunch hour.

22:01.153 --> 22:02.237
(clearing throat)

22:02.320 --> 22:03.739
I'm gonna go check out.

22:03.822 --> 22:05.407
I already did that, David.

22:05.490 --> 22:09.161
We just got to get going now
to the, uh, to the thing.

22:10.287 --> 22:11.204
I got this thing--

22:11.288 --> 22:12.122
it's this, uh, this, uh...

22:12.205 --> 22:14.082
It's like a... a meeting
up at the station.

22:14.166 --> 22:15.083
Is it important?

22:15.167 --> 22:16.918
Yeah, it's my boss.

22:17.002 --> 22:19.087
I thought you owned the club.

22:19.171 --> 22:20.130
{\an1}DYLAN:
You have a great memory.

22:20.213 --> 22:23.258
Actually, um, David works
for the radio station.

22:23.341 --> 22:25.302
Oh.

22:25.385 --> 22:26.553
{\an3}So, um...

22:26.636 --> 22:29.723
Well, that's it pretty much.

22:34.644 --> 22:36.938
So, you, you'll call, right,

22:37.022 --> 22:39.608
{\an3}when you know
you're coming back?

22:39.691 --> 22:43.487
Okay.

22:43.570 --> 22:45.614
{\an1}Um... bye.

22:49.659 --> 22:53.413
So, good luck...
with your meeting.

22:53.497 --> 22:54.790
Thanks.

23:03.882 --> 23:05.801
I read the environmental report.

23:05.884 --> 23:08.095
Look, it doesn't have
to come out in court.

23:08.178 --> 23:09.638
No, no, let it.

23:09.721 --> 23:10.806
{\an1}You're not fighting
the charges?

23:10.889 --> 23:11.973
Before my father died,

23:12.057 --> 23:13.433
he apologized for
everything he did.

23:13.517 --> 23:15.310
He didn't mention this.

23:15.394 --> 23:17.771
You don't know what
went on in his head.

23:17.854 --> 23:19.981
The pressure
I don't care.

23:20.065 --> 23:22.609
Look, I found this stuff
when I cleared out his office.

23:22.692 --> 23:25.320
You know, I have enough
to push a settlement.

23:25.403 --> 23:26.613
I'm sure there's more.

23:26.696 --> 23:28.031
Noah...

23:28.115 --> 23:29.449
Matt, I want to do this, man.

23:29.533 --> 23:31.493
{\an3}Come on.

23:31.576 --> 23:32.786
All right.

23:41.545 --> 23:42.838
STEVE:
Damn.

23:42.921 --> 23:44.548
(compuUgh.beeps)

23:44.631 --> 23:45.841
{\an3}DONNA:
Steve, hey.

23:45.924 --> 23:47.008
Hi.

23:47.092 --> 23:49.636
{\an3}Where would your
real estate listings be?

23:49.719 --> 23:51.054
Tomorrow's ad copy
is on Janet's desk.

23:51.138 --> 23:52.347
Trying to get a jump?

23:52.430 --> 23:53.974
Um, I lost the realtor's card,

23:54.057 --> 23:56.309
and I can't seem to remember
the name of her firm.

23:56.393 --> 23:57.811
Really, you guys
are really serious

23:57.894 --> 23:59.396
about moving in together.

23:59.479 --> 24:03.400
Do you think
it was easier for you

24:03.483 --> 24:05.819
to be committed to Janet since
you have dated so many women?

24:05.902 --> 24:07.028
I don't know.

24:07.112 --> 24:09.322
I don't think
it'll ever be easy.

24:09.406 --> 24:10.699
I've only been
with two guys.

24:10.782 --> 24:13.034
Noah and David, two.

24:13.118 --> 24:17.414
You're always dreaming
of finding "the one."

24:17.497 --> 24:21.418
{\an1}Yeah... and then when
you find the one,

24:21.501 --> 24:24.421
{\an1}you realize it might
be the last one.

24:24.504 --> 24:27.465
DONNA:
Noah's just so ready.

24:27.549 --> 24:28.341
I feel like if I don't catch up,

24:28.425 --> 24:30.051
I might as well
be going in reverse.

24:30.135 --> 24:32.053
I want to do this.

24:32.137 --> 24:35.390
I'm... I'm gonna call
the realtor.

24:35.473 --> 24:37.893
I'm gonna call Janet.

24:45.984 --> 24:50.572
Um... I think I'm just gonna...

24:50.655 --> 24:52.532
I'm just gonna
call from the car.

24:52.616 --> 24:54.326
Okay, I'll see you later.

25:01.166 --> 25:03.376
God!

25:05.503 --> 25:08.381
(dialing)

25:10.175 --> 25:12.928
(with deep voice):
Hello, Lilly?

25:13.011 --> 25:14.596
This is Steve Sanders.

25:14.679 --> 25:17.098
I got your number
from the Love Fisher.

25:17.182 --> 25:18.433
(phone ringing)

25:18.516 --> 25:19.267
Wayne?

25:19.351 --> 25:20.435
Hi, it's Donna.

25:20.519 --> 25:21.436
Hey.

25:21.519 --> 25:23.438
I wasn't gonna call, but...

25:23.521 --> 25:29.402
um, I just, I kind of need
to talk to you in person.

25:29.486 --> 25:30.487
And I want to see you.

25:44.251 --> 25:46.586
Is something wrong?

25:46.670 --> 25:49.297
No.

25:53.009 --> 25:54.094
{\an3}What?

25:54.177 --> 25:56.513
Nothing.

25:58.556 --> 26:01.101
What is it,(sighs)

26:01.184 --> 26:02.477
You totally led her on.

26:02.560 --> 26:04.271
No, boy meets girl, it happens.

26:04.354 --> 26:07.315
Dylan, you told her
you would see her again soon.

26:07.399 --> 26:08.316
And I might.

26:08.400 --> 26:09.818
You never know.

26:09.901 --> 26:11.486
{\an1}I don't know
how you manage

26:11.569 --> 26:15.365
to not care
about hurting anybody,

26:15.448 --> 26:17.993
you know, it's, it's beyond me.

26:18.076 --> 26:19.327
{\an3}One night at a
time, David.

26:19.411 --> 26:21.371
It was just a one-night stand.

26:21.454 --> 26:23.206
What if you never
see Mary again?

26:23.290 --> 26:25.208
That'd be fine with me.

26:25.292 --> 26:26.751
{\an1}You had such a
great thing

26:26.835 --> 26:28.378
with Gina, you know?

26:28.461 --> 26:29.921
And you just totally blow it off

26:30.005 --> 26:31.756
{\an1}and I mean,
that was something

26:31.840 --> 26:33.883
that any guy would kill for.

26:33.967 --> 26:35.844
Present company excluded?

26:37.762 --> 26:39.097
I think you blew

26:39.180 --> 26:41.016
a good thing for nothing,
all right? that's it.

26:41.099 --> 26:43.143
Yeah, well, I'll tell you what.

26:43.226 --> 26:44.728
{\an3}I thought I was living
with a roommate,

26:44.811 --> 26:47.355
not a hall moniYep.

26:51.401 --> 26:52.819
(phone ringing)

26:52.902 --> 26:54.321
(sighs)

26:56.281 --> 26:57.866
Yeah?

26:57.949 --> 26:59.701
Dylan, it's Mary.

26:59.784 --> 27:01.411
Uh, uh, no, Mary,
this is, this is David.

27:01.494 --> 27:03.038
Dylan isn't home.

27:03.121 --> 27:05.707
Well, I have a friend I've
been meaning to visit in L.A.,

27:05.790 --> 27:07.375
and I thought
maybe I'd drop by.

27:07.459 --> 27:08.710
Really, you're coming to L.A.?

27:08.793 --> 27:10.211
You want to stop by here?

27:10.295 --> 27:11.838
Unless you think I shouldn't.

27:11.921 --> 27:14.382
No, you know what,
I think you should.

27:14.466 --> 27:15.925
Absolutely.

27:16.009 --> 27:18.970
Dylan was just saying how
he can't wait to see you.

27:19.054 --> 27:20.555
Could you give me your address?

27:20.638 --> 27:22.349
Yeah. You got a pen?

27:22.432 --> 27:25.101
Yeah, hold on. I'll get one.

27:25.185 --> 27:27.354
{\an5}MATT:
What do you say
we call it quits, huh?

27:30.648 --> 27:32.901
Would you stop already?

27:32.984 --> 27:34.903
There's nothing else here.

27:34.986 --> 27:38.073
Oh, God, of mementos.

27:38.156 --> 27:39.407
Take it home.

27:39.491 --> 27:41.159
Put it under your bed.

27:43.286 --> 27:45.372
What you got there?

27:45.455 --> 27:47.415
My Little League
certificate, man.

27:47.499 --> 27:49.292
We got them every year,
you know?

27:49.376 --> 27:51.753
I used to think
it was pretty cool.

27:51.836 --> 27:53.713
Apparently, so did your dad.

27:53.797 --> 27:54.464
(chuckles)

27:55.423 --> 27:57.759
Hey. I stopped by the house.

27:57.842 --> 27:59.761
Steve said you guys
pulled an all-nighter.

27:59.844 --> 28:01.721
Uh, well, Noah did.

28:01.805 --> 28:03.306
{\an3}I slept for a
good 20 minutes.

28:03.390 --> 28:05.100
Did you find anything?

28:05.183 --> 28:06.851
Yeah, I think we did.

28:07.852 --> 28:09.562
So, what'd you tell the realtor?

28:09.646 --> 28:13.149
That's, uh, what I came by
to talk to you about.

28:13.233 --> 28:16.027
Okay, um, yes or no?

28:17.862 --> 28:18.780
No.

28:18.863 --> 28:20.573
I guess we have nothing
to talk about, then.

28:20.657 --> 28:22.951
Maybe this just
isn't a good time.

28:23.034 --> 28:24.577
It's a perfect time to move in.

28:24.661 --> 28:27.580
To commit, the two of us,
you know?

28:27.664 --> 28:29.416
At least I thought it was.

28:29.499 --> 28:30.417
You're not letting me
explain here.

28:30.500 --> 28:31.626
No, I guess I'm not.

28:38.425 --> 28:39.968
Oh, let me guess,

28:40.051 --> 28:42.262
{\an3}your Pee Wee
football certificate.

28:42.345 --> 28:44.097
Not quite, Matt, not quite.

28:44.180 --> 28:45.682
What is it?

28:52.355 --> 28:53.440
Oh, my God.

28:53.523 --> 28:54.649
That's right.

